Description: Corroded copper alloy fragment of a figure of a cat-headed (?) winged demon (?) with spread wings.
Curator's comments: W.M.F. Petrie, Tanis ii, Nebesheh and Defenneh, p. 80 § 80 mentions the "upper part of a winged cat-headed Bast (?)"
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 80 § 80) (?)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.49, p.56, p.177, pl.19)
Condition: Corroded, incomplete (feet, arms and one wing broken and missing).
